764	\label{sec:IsHModuleHomFinite_producer}
765	
766	Iter-046 collapses the originally-multi-iteration step (1) (linearised constant-sheaf / global-sections adjunction \lstinline{LinearEquiv}) plus the iter-047-planned producer-instance assembly into a single iteration via three observations:
767	\begin{itemize}
768	  \item Mathlib's \lstinline{Adjunction.homAddEquiv} (\lstinline{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Adjunction/Additive.lean}) lifts the bare $\mathtt{homEquiv}$ to an additive equivalence under $F.\mathtt{Additive}$. The further upgrade to $\LinearEquiv\,k$ (under $F.\mathtt{Linear}\,k$) is a one-liner via $(\mathtt{adj.homEquiv}).\mathtt{injective} + \mathtt{simp}\,[\mathtt{adj.homEquiv\_unit}]$, mirroring Mathlib's \lstinline{left_adjoint_additive}. This is project-local Mathlib gap-fills \lstinline{Adjunction.left_adjoint_linear} + \lstinline{Adjunction.right_adjoint_linear} + \lstinline{Adjunction.homLinearEquiv}.
769	  \item The $\Functor.\Linear\,k$ propagation chain --- $\mathtt{Functor.const}$ Linear (one-liner), $\mathtt{presheafToSheaf}$ Linear (via \lstinline{sheafificationAdjunction.left_adjoint_linear}), $\mathtt{constantSheaf}$ Linear (via composition), $\Sheaf.\Gamma$ Linear (via \lstinline{constantSheafΓAdj.right_adjoint_linear}) --- is mechanical.
770	  \item The Hom-from-$k$ upgrade $(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k \to M) \equivl{k} M$ for $M : \ModuleCat\,k$ is a Mathlib-already-existing one-liner via \lstinline{ModuleCat.homLinearEquiv} composed with \lstinline{LinearMap.ringLmapEquivSelf}.
771	\end{itemize}
772	
773	The producer instance combines all three with iter-045's evaluation iso to land $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,k\,((\mathtt{constantSheaf}).\mathtt{obj}\,(\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k) \to \toModuleKSheaf\,C)$ from the iter-044 geometric Stein input. Once registered as a typeclass instance, iter-043's curve consumer \lstinline{module_finite_HModule_zero_of_isHModuleHomFinite_curve} fires automatically on $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,k\,(\HModule\,k\,(\toModuleKSheaf\,C)\,0)$ queries --- closing the H$^0$ side of the genus-finrank Module.Finite ladder.
